  "prompt": "I got placed in TCS's EIS stream in my campus placement. Will I get a job in EIS or in IT?",
  "response": "Congratulations on getting placed in TCS's EIS (Enterprise Intelligent Solutions) stream! Generally, when you've been placed in a specific stream like EIS, you are expected to work in that area. However, the actual job role can depend on several factors, including the company's project requirements, your skills and interests, and any additional training you might receive.\n\nIt's possible that, depending on the needs of the organization, you could work on IT-related projects as part of your position in EIS, especially if those projects intersect with enterprise solutions. If you have a specific career path in mind, it may be beneficial to discuss your career goals with your managers or HR representatives once you start. They'll be able to guide you on what to expect and any opportunities for development within the company.",
